sequenceDiagram
    participant WT1 as Worktree Agent 1<br>.worktrees/loop_001/
    participant WT2 as Worktree Agent 2<br>.worktrees/loop_002/
    participant WT3 as Worktree Agent 3<br>.worktrees/loop_003/
    participant MQ as Merge Queue<br>.ralph/merge-queue.jsonl
    participant PL as Primary Loop<br>(holds loop.lock)
    participant GIT as Git Repository

    Note over WT1,GIT: Phase 1 -- Isolation (git worktrees, shared .git, symlinked specs)

    par Parallel Execution
        WT1->>WT1: Hat iterations (plan, code, review)
        WT2->>WT2: Hat iterations (plan, code, review)
        WT3->>WT3: Hat iterations (plan, code, review)
    end

    Note over WT1,GIT: Phase 2 -- Completion and Enqueue

    WT1->>MQ: enqueue(loop_001, prompt)
    Note over MQ: Event: Queued { loop_id, prompt, timestamp }

    WT3->>MQ: enqueue(loop_003, prompt)
    Note over MQ: Event: Queued { loop_id, prompt, timestamp }

    Note over WT2: Still executing...

    Note over PL,GIT: Phase 3 -- Merge Processing (FIFO from queue)

    PL->>MQ: next_pending()
    MQ-->>PL: Entry: loop_001

    PL->>MQ: flock() acquire
    PL->>MQ: mark_merging(loop_001, pid)
    Note over MQ: Event: Merging { loop_id, pid }

    PL->>GIT: git merge loop_001 branch

    alt Success -- No Conflicts
        GIT-->>PL: Merge clean
        PL->>MQ: mark_merged(loop_001, commit_sha)
        Note over MQ: Event: Merged { loop_id, commit_sha }
        PL->>GIT: remove_worktree(loop_001)
    else Conflict -- Spawn Merge Ralph
        GIT-->>PL: Conflict detected
        PL->>PL: Spawn merge-ralph agent
        PL->>GIT: Agent resolves conflicts
        PL->>GIT: git add + git commit
        PL->>MQ: mark_merged(loop_001, commit_sha)
        Note over MQ: Event: Merged { loop_id, commit_sha }
        PL->>GIT: remove_worktree(loop_001)
    else Failure -- Unresolvable
        GIT-->>PL: Merge failed
        PL->>GIT: git merge --abort
        PL->>MQ: mark_failed(loop_001, error_msg)
        Note over MQ: Event: Failed { loop_id, error }
    end

    PL->>MQ: flock() release

    PL->>MQ: next_pending()
    MQ-->>PL: Entry: loop_003

    PL->>MQ: mark_merging(loop_003, pid)
    PL->>GIT: git merge loop_003 branch
    GIT-->>PL: Merge clean
    PL->>MQ: mark_merged(loop_003, commit_sha)
    PL->>GIT: remove_worktree(loop_003)

    WT2->>MQ: enqueue(loop_002, prompt)
    Note over MQ: Event: Queued { loop_id, prompt, timestamp }

    PL->>MQ: next_pending()
    MQ-->>PL: Entry: loop_002
    PL->>GIT: git merge loop_002 branch
    GIT-->>PL: Merge clean
    PL->>MQ: mark_merged(loop_002, commit_sha)
    PL->>GIT: remove_worktree(loop_002)

    Note over MQ: Append-only JSONL preserves full<br>event history for replay and debugging
